{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":975,"text":"Today 40 million Americans are indebted\nfor their passage to the new economy."},{"time":8039,"text":"Too poor to pay their way through college,"},{"time":10167,"text":"they now owe lenders\nmore than one trillion US dollars."},{"time":15709,"text":"They do find what jobs they can get"},{"time":17972,"text":"to pay off a debt\nthat is secured on their person."},{"time":21201,"text":"In America,"},{"time":23273,"text":"even a bankrupt gambler\ngets a second chance."},{"time":30351,"text":"But it is nearly impossible"},{"time":33177,"text":"for an American to get discharged\ntheir student loan debts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":40421,"text":"Once upon a time in America,"},{"time":43165,"text":"going to college did not mean\ngraduating with debt."},{"time":47299,"text":"My friend Paul's father\ngraduated from Colorado State University"},{"time":52609,"text":"on the GI Bill."},{"time":55546,"text":"For his generation,"},{"time":57158,"text":"higher education was free or almost free,"},{"time":60030,"text":"because it was thought of\nas a public good."},{"time":63676,"text":"Not anymore."},{"time":66171,"text":"When Paul also graduated\nfrom Colorado State University,"},{"time":70291,"text":"he paid for his English degree\nby working part-time."},{"time":74164,"text":"30 years ago,"},{"time":75339,"text":"higher education tuition\nwas affordable, reasonable,"},{"time":78030,"text":"and what debts you accumulated,\nyou paid off by graduation date."},{"time":81952,"text":"Not anymore."},{"time":83829,"text":"Paul's daughter followed in his footsteps,"},{"time":87227,"text":"but with one difference:"},{"time":88552,"text":"when she graduated five years ago,"},{"time":91068,"text":"it was with a whopping debt."}]},{"cues":[{"time":93179,"text":"Students like Kate have to take on a loan"},{"time":96545,"text":"because the cost of higher education\nhas become unaffordable"},{"time":99768,"text":"for many if not most American families."},{"time":104427,"text":"But so what?"},{"time":106117,"text":"Getting into debt to buy\nan expensive education"},{"time":108689,"text":"is not all bad if you could pay it off"},{"time":111475,"text":"with the increased income\nthat you earned from it."},{"time":115266,"text":"But that's where the rubber\nmeets the road."},{"time":119652,"text":"Even a college grad\nearned 10 percent more in 2001"},{"time":125272,"text":"than she did in 2013."}]},{"cues":[{"time":127984,"text":"So ..."},{"time":129779,"text":"tuition costs up,"},{"time":131462,"text":"public funding down,"},{"time":133009,"text":"family incomes diminished,"},{"time":135470,"text":"personal incomes weak."},{"time":138241,"text":"Is it any wonder that more\nthan a quarter of those who must"},{"time":142670,"text":"cannot make their student loan payments?"},{"time":146852,"text":"The worst of times\ncan be the best of times,"},{"time":149853,"text":"because certain truths flash up\nin ways that you can't ignore."},{"time":154446,"text":"I want to speak of three of them today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":157571,"text":"1.2 trillion dollars of debts for diplomas"},{"time":161469,"text":"make it abundantly obvious"},{"time":163958,"text":"that higher education\nis a consumer product you can buy."},{"time":168283,"text":"All of us talk about education\njust as the economists do now,"},{"time":173125,"text":"as an investment that you make\nto improve the human stock"},{"time":177630,"text":"by training them for work."},{"time":179812,"text":"As an investment you make\nto sort and classify people"},{"time":184559,"text":"so that employers\ncan hire them more easily."},{"time":188396,"text":"The U.S. News &amp; World Report\nranks colleges"},{"time":191818,"text":"just as the consumer report\nrates washing machines."},{"time":195095,"text":"The language is peppered with barbarisms."},{"time":198882,"text":"Teachers are called \"service providers,\""},{"time":202287,"text":"students are called \"consumers.\""},{"time":205509,"text":"Sociology and Shakespeare\nand soccer and science,"},{"time":209414,"text":"all of these are \"content.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":213318,"text":"Student debt is profitable."},{"time":214723,"text":"Only not on you."},{"time":217961,"text":"Your debt fattens the profit\nof the student loan industry."},{"time":222040,"text":"The two 800-pound gorillas of which --"},{"time":224501,"text":"Sallie Mae and Navient --"},{"time":226588,"text":"posted last year a combined profit\nof 1.2 billion dollars."},{"time":232568,"text":"And just like home mortgages,"},{"time":235164,"text":"student loans can be bundled\nand packaged and sliced and diced,"},{"time":238374,"text":"and sold on Wall Street."},{"time":240369,"text":"And colleges and universities"},{"time":241989,"text":"that invest in these securitized loans"},{"time":246170,"text":"profit twice."},{"time":247735,"text":"Once from your tuition,"},{"time":249180,"text":"and then again from the interest on debt."}]},{"cues":[{"time":253108,"text":"With all that money to be made,"},{"time":255498,"text":"are we surprised that some\nin the higher education business"},{"time":261109,"text":"have begun to engage in false advertising,"},{"time":263205,"text":"in bait and switch ..."},{"time":266585,"text":"in exploiting the very ignorance\nthat they pretend to educate?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":272144,"text":"Third:"},{"time":273678,"text":"diplomas are a brand."},{"time":275741,"text":"Many years ago my teacher wrote,"},{"time":278116,"text":"\"When students are treated as consumers,"},{"time":280681,"text":"they're made prisoners\nof addiction and envy.\""},{"time":287794,"text":"Just as consumers can be sold and resold\nupgraded versions of an iPhone,"},{"time":292359,"text":"so also people can be sold\nmore and more education."},{"time":296807,"text":"College is the new high school,"},{"time":298697,"text":"we already say that."},{"time":301408,"text":"But why stop there?"},{"time":302831,"text":"People can be upsold\non certifications and recertifications,"},{"time":306332,"text":"master's degrees, doctoral degrees."}]},{"cues":[{"time":311436,"text":"Higher education is also marketed\nas a status object."},{"time":316634,"text":"Buy a degree,"},{"time":317809,"text":"much like you do a Lexus\nof a Louis Vuitton bag,"},{"time":321020,"text":"to distinguish yourself from others."},{"time":322838,"text":"So you can be the object\nof envy of others."},{"time":326669,"text":"Diplomas are a brand."}]},{"cues":[{"time":329034,"text":"But these truths are often times\nhidden by a very noisy sales pitch."},{"time":336535,"text":"There is not a day that goes by"},{"time":338195,"text":"without some policy guy\non television telling us,"},{"time":343256,"text":"\"A college degree is absolutely essential"},{"time":345304,"text":"to get on that up escalator\nto a middle-class life.\""},{"time":348890,"text":"And the usual evidence offered\nis the college premium:"},{"time":352592,"text":"a college grad who makes on average\n56 percent more than a high school grad."}]},{"cues":[{"time":358425,"text":"Let's look at that number more carefully,"},{"time":360497,"text":"because on the face of it,"},{"time":361847,"text":"it seems to belie the stories we all hear"},{"time":365215,"text":"about college grads\nworking as baristas and cashiers."},{"time":370545,"text":"Of 100 people who enroll\nin any form of post-secondary education,"},{"time":375720,"text":"45 do not complete it in a timely fashion,"},{"time":378792,"text":"for a number of reasons,\nincluding financial."},{"time":382275,"text":"Of the 55 that do graduate,"},{"time":384212,"text":"two will remain unemployed,"},{"time":386284,"text":"and another 18 are underemployed."},{"time":390058,"text":"So, college grads earn more\nthan high school grads,"},{"time":393757,"text":"but does it pay for the exorbitant tuition"},{"time":396774,"text":"and the lost wages while at college?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":399661,"text":"Now even economists admit"},{"time":402281,"text":"going to college pays off\nfor only those who complete it."},{"time":408095,"text":"But that's only because high school wages\nhave been cut to the bone,"},{"time":412151,"text":"for decades now."},{"time":415369,"text":"For decades,"},{"time":417282,"text":"workers with a high school degree"},{"time":419663,"text":"have been denied a fair share\nof what they have produced."},{"time":424480,"text":"And had they received as they should have,"},{"time":427409,"text":"then going to college would have been\na bad investment for many."},{"time":431386,"text":"College premium?"},{"time":433941,"text":"I think it's a high school discount."}]},{"cues":[{"time":436688,"text":"Two out of three people who enroll\nare not going to find an adequate job."},{"time":441756,"text":"And the future, for them,\ndoesn't look particularly promising --"},{"time":444891,"text":"in fact, it's downright bleak."},{"time":446637,"text":"And it is they who are going to suffer"},{"time":450541,"text":"the most punishing forms of student debt."},{"time":454002,"text":"And it is they,"},{"time":455177,"text":"curiously and sadly,"},{"time":456582,"text":"who are marketed most loudly\nabout this college premium thing."},{"time":461986,"text":"That's not just cynical marketing,"},{"time":464407,"text":"that's cruel."}]},{"cues":[{"time":467277,"text":"So what do we do?"},{"time":469279,"text":"What if students and parents treated\nhigher education as a consumer product?"},{"time":476199,"text":"Everybody else seems to."},{"time":478686,"text":"Then, like any other consumer product,"},{"time":480972,"text":"you would demand to know\nwhat you're paying for."},{"time":483495,"text":"When you buy medicines,"},{"time":484734,"text":"you get a list of side effects."},{"time":486673,"text":"When you buy a higher educational product,"},{"time":488809,"text":"you should have a warning label"},{"time":490467,"text":"that allows consumers to choose,"},{"time":492683,"text":"make informed choices."},{"time":494838,"text":"When you buy a car,"},{"time":496054,"text":"it tells you how many\nmiles per gallon to expect."},{"time":499188,"text":"Who knows what to expect"},{"time":500658,"text":"from a degree say, in Canadian Studies."},{"time":504806,"text":"There is such a thing, by the way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":508989,"text":"What if there was an app for that?"},{"time":514402,"text":"One that linked up the cost of a major\nto the expected income."},{"time":520208,"text":"Let's call it Income-Based Tuition or IBT."},{"time":522598,"text":"One of you make this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":524144,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":525707,"text":"Discover your reality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":527463,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":529796,"text":"There are three advantages,"},{"time":531249,"text":"three benefits to Income-Based Tuition."},{"time":535232,"text":"Any user can figure out"},{"time":537145,"text":"how much money he or she will make\nfrom a given college and major."},{"time":541105,"text":"Such informed users"},{"time":542471,"text":"are unlikely to fall victim\nto the huckster's ploy,"},{"time":546440,"text":"to the sales pitch."},{"time":547874,"text":"But also to choose wisely."},{"time":549604,"text":"Why would anybody pay more for college"},{"time":552030,"text":"than let's say, 15 percent\nof the additional income they earn?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":557040,"text":"There's a second benefit\nto Income-Based Tuition."},{"time":559780,"text":"By tying the cost to the income,"},{"time":562764,"text":"college administrators would be forced\nto manage costs better,"},{"time":567209,"text":"to find innovative ways to do so."},{"time":569573,"text":"For instance,"},{"time":570751,"text":"all of you students here pay roughly\nthe same tuition for every major."},{"time":575478,"text":"That is manifestly unfair,\nand should change."},{"time":580295,"text":"An engineering student uses more resources"},{"time":584240,"text":"and facilities and labs and faculty"},{"time":586673,"text":"than a philosophy student."},{"time":589581,"text":"But the philosophy student,\nas a consequence,"},{"time":591709,"text":"is subsidizing the engineering student."},{"time":594300,"text":"Who then, by the way,\ngoes on and earns more money."},{"time":597015,"text":"Why should two people\nbuy the same product,"},{"time":600746,"text":"pay the same,"},{"time":601945,"text":"but one person receive\nhalf or a third of the service."},{"time":606448,"text":"In fact, college grads, some majors,"},{"time":610543,"text":"pay 25 percent of their income\nservicing their student debt,"},{"time":614187,"text":"while others pay five percent."},{"time":617510,"text":"That kind if inequity would end\nwhen majors are priced more correctly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":623042,"text":"Now of course, all this data --"},{"time":625225,"text":"and one of you is going to do this, right?"},{"time":627323,"text":"All this data has to be well designed,"},{"time":629194,"text":"maybe audited by public accounting firms"},{"time":631316,"text":"to avoid statistical lies."},{"time":633292,"text":"We know about statistics, right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":636766,"text":"But be that as it may,"},{"time":638013,"text":"the third and biggest benefit\nof Income-Based Tuition,"},{"time":642418,"text":"is it would free Americans from the fear\nand the fact of financial ruin"},{"time":647871,"text":"because they bought a defective product."}]},{"cues":[{"time":650813,"text":"Perhaps, in time,"},{"time":653156,"text":"young and old Americans may rediscover,"},{"time":655428,"text":"as the gentleman said earlier,"},{"time":657649,"text":"their curiosity, their love of learning --"},{"time":659712,"text":"begin to study what they love,"},{"time":661173,"text":"love what they study,"},{"time":662376,"text":"follow their passion ..."},{"time":664577,"text":"getting stimulated by their intelligence,"},{"time":667070,"text":"follow paths of inquiry\nthat they really want to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":670848,"text":"After all, it was Eric and Kevin,"},{"time":675322,"text":"two years ago,"},{"time":677498,"text":"just exactly these kinds of young men,"},{"time":680954,"text":"who prompted me and worked with me,"},{"time":683000,"text":"and still do,"},{"time":684585,"text":"in the study of indebted\nstudents in America."}]},{"cues":[{"time":689272,"text":"Thank you for your attention."}]},{"cues":[{"time":690827,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}